data.title: California Cattlemen's Foundation
data.text:
ADVOCACY. EDUCATION. RESEARCH.

The California Cattlemen’s Foundation is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization whose mission is to strengthen the future of California’s beef industry through investment in advocacy, education, and research programs designed to support sustainable cattle production. Doing this will preserve the proud heritage established by California’s cattlemen and cattlewomen and will ensure that future generations are prepared to face the challenges ahead.

ADVOCACY WORK

EDUCATION OUTREACH

What Producers Are Saying About Their Experience with RTAP

“I reached out to the Rancher Technical Assistance Program and was provided with specific information about my SB 88 water measurement and reporting question. The compliance process was explained and resources and links were sent to me. I recommend RTAP to any rancher with regulatory compliance questions.”

— A.G., Inyo County

“The RTAP team did an excellent job of explaining stockpond registrations and their regulations. They helped clarify how the State Water Board defines a stockpond.”

— M.S., Siskiyou County
